## Step 3: Configure Database and Prisma
1. Create a `.env` file in the project root:
   ```
   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://username:password@localhost:5432/myproject?schema=public"
   ```
   Replace with your PostgreSQL credentials.

2. Initialize Prisma:
   ```bash
   npx prisma init
   ```

3. Define the schema in `prisma/schema.prisma`:
   ```prisma
   generator client {
     provider = "prisma-client-js"
   }

   datasource db {
     provider = "postgresql"
     url      = env("DATABASE_URL")
   }

   model Post {
     id        Int      @id @default(autoincrement())
     title     String
     content   String?
     published Boolean  @defaults(false)
     authorId  Int
     author    User     @relation(fields: [authorId], references: [id])
     createdAt DateTime @default(now())
   }

   model User {
     id    Int     @id @default(autoincrement())
     email String  @unique
     name  String?
     posts Post[]
   }
   ```

4. Run migrations:
   ```bash
   npx prisma db push
   npx prisma generate
   ```

