## 2️⃣ ASX-BLOCK-LIBRARY.json

Drop this at the root as `ASX-BLOCK-LIBRARY.json` (or under `/config/` if you prefer).

It matches the blocks from the docs and gives you a nice machine-readable registry.

```json
{
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "generated_at": "K'UHUL-GODMODE",
  "blocks": {
    "KUHUL_GODMODE_OS": {
      "name": "K'UHUL GOD MODE OS",
      "category": "core_os",
      "kind": ["ui", "engine"],
      "description": "Multi-hive training cockpit: TPU-OS, KLH router, SCXQ2 engine, PRIME dashboard, multi-agent panels, live metrics, and SVG hive core.",
      "entry_hint": "ui/k-uhul-godmode.html"
    },
    "PRIME_COCKPIT_V1": {
      "name": "PRIME Cockpit v1",
      "category": "core_os",
      "kind": ["ui"],
      "description": "5-panel PRIME command center for model manager, plugin store, vision, Cline tasks, and external LLM fusion.",
      "entry_hint": "ui/prime-cockpit.html"
    },
    "PRIME_MATRIX_LOGIN": {
      "name": "PRIME Matrix Login",
      "category": "core_os",
      "kind": ["ui"],
      "description": "Matrix-rain identity gate; ASX Wallet + Web Crypto PIN + Google OAuth dual-login.",
      "entry_hint": "ui/prime-login.html"
    },
    "ASX_KERNEL_ROOT": {
      "name": "ASX Kernel Root",
      "category": "core_os",
      "kind": ["engine"],
      "description": "Minimal kernel block: manifest.json + sw.klh + XJSON runtime hooks + SCXQ2 loader.",
