### 3.2 `asx-blocks.scx` — SCXQ2-Style Compressed Variant

This doesn’t have to inline the giant HTML bodies; instead it compresses:

* Block IDs → short glyphs
* Categories → single-symbol tags
* CSS profiles → short profile keys

So your runtime can map tiny SCXQ2 tokens back into full blocks using the JSON registry.

```text
; asx-blocks.scx
; SCXQ2-style symbolic registry for ASX Blocks
; (Short glyphs → full IDs, categories, and CSS profiles)

#DICT
  B0 = KUHUL_GODMODE_OS
  B1 = PRIME_COCKPIT_V1
  B2 = PRIME_MATRIX_LOGIN
  B3 = ASX_KERNEL_ROOT

  B4 = MX2LM_TRAINER
  B5 = TPU_VIRTUAL_CORE
  B6 = ULTRA_FUSION_LOOP
  B7 = ULTRA_DATASET_ENGINE

  B8 = FINTECHBRO_QUANT_UI
  B9 = HIVE_CORE_SVG
  BA = CORNMAZE_AI_MAP
  BB = WASTELAND_HUD
  BC = RISK_MAP_UI

  BD = ARENA_BATTLE_ENGINE
  BE = RISK_CORE_SYSTEM
  BF = TRICKSTER_AI

  C0 = XJSON_DOCSET
  C1 = ATOMIC_HTML_GUIDE
  C2 = SCXQ2_MANUAL
  C3 = ASX_FULLSTACK_GUIDE

  U0 = ULTRA_AGENT_FUSION_SCRIPT
  U1 = ULTRA_BATTLEMODE_GENERATOR
  U2 = ULTRA_COMPILER_GENERATOR
  U3 = ULTRA_DATASET_GENERATOR
  U4 = ULTRA_FUSION_JUDGE
